\v 15 and \x + \xo 1:15 \xt ch. 6:19; See 1 Kgs. 10:1\x*the Sabeans fell upon them and took them and struck down the servants\f + \fr 1:15 \ft Hebrew \fq the young men\ft ; also verses 16, 17\f* with the edge of the sword, and I alone have escaped to tell you.”
\v 16 While he was yet speaking, there came another and said, \x + \xo 1:16 \xt 2 Kgs. 1:12\x*“The fire of God fell from heaven and burned up the sheep and the servants and consumed them, and I alone have escaped to tell you.”
\v 17 While he was yet speaking, there came another and said, \x + \xo 1:17 \xt Gen. 11:28; 2 Kgs. 24:2 \x*“The Chaldeans formed \x + \xo 1:17 \xt [Judg. 7:16; 1 Sam. 11:11]\x*three groups and made a raid on the camels and took them and struck down the servants with the edge of the sword, and I alone have escaped to tell you.”
\v 18 While he was yet speaking, there came another and said, \x + \xo 1:18 \xt ver. 4, 13\x*“Your sons and daughters were eating and drinking wine in their oldest brother’s house,
\v 19 and behold, a great wind came across \x + \xo 1:19 \xt Isa. 21:1; Jer. 4:11; Hos. 13:15\x*the wilderness and struck the four corners of the house, and it fell upon the young people, and they are dead, and I alone have escaped to tell you.”
\p
\v 20 Then Job arose and \x + \xo 1:20 \xt See Gen. 37:29 \x*tore his \x + \xo 1:20 \xt Ezra 9:3 \x*robe and \x + \xo 1:20 \xt Jer. 7:29 \x*shaved his head \x + \xo 1:20 \xt [1 Pet. 5:6]\x*and fell on the ground and worshiped.
\v 21 And he said, \x + \xo 1:21 \xt Eccles. 5:15; [Ps. 49:17; 1 Tim. 6:7] \x*“Naked I came from my mother’s womb, and naked shall I \x + \xo 1:21 \xt [Gen. 3:19; Ps. 90:3; Eccles. 12:7] \x*return. The \nd Lord\nd* \x + \xo 1:21 \xt [Eccles. 5:19; James 1:17] \x*gave, and the \nd Lord\nd* has taken away; \x + \xo 1:21 \xt Ps. 113:2; Dan. 2:20; [Eph. 5:20; 1 Thess. 5:18]\x*blessed be the name of the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\p
\v 22 \x + \xo 1:22 \xt ch. 2:10 \x*In all this Job did not sin or charge God with \x + \xo 1:22 \xt ch. 24:12\x*wrong.
\c 2
\s1 Satan Attacks Job’s Health
\p \v 1 Again \x + \xo 2:1 \xt ch. 1:6\x*there was a day when the sons of God came to present themselves before the \nd Lord\nd*, and Satan also came among them to present himself before the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 2 And the \nd Lord\nd* said to Satan, “From where have you come?” Satan answered the \nd Lord\nd* and said, “From going to and fro on the earth, and from walking up and down on it.”
\v 3 And the \nd Lord\nd* said to Satan, “Have you considered my servant Job, that there is none like him on the earth, a blameless and upright man, who fears God and turns away from evil? He still \x + \xo 2:3 \xt ver. 9; [ch. 27:5, 6] \x*holds fast his integrity, although you incited me against him to destroy him \x + \xo 2:3 \xt ch. 9:17\x*without reason.”
\v 4 Then Satan answered the \nd Lord\nd* and said, “Skin for skin! All that a man has he will give for his life.
\v 5 But \x + \xo 2:5 \xt ch. 1:11 \x*stretch out your hand and touch his bone and his flesh, and he will \x + \xo 2:5 \xt ch. 1:5\x*curse you to your face.”
\v 6 And the \nd Lord\nd* said to Satan, “Behold, he is in your hand; only spare his life.”
\p
\v 7 So Satan went out from the presence of the \nd Lord\nd* and struck Job with loathsome \x + \xo 2:7 \xt Ex. 9:9; Lev. 13:18; [Deut. 28:27] \x*sores from \x + \xo 2:7 \xt Deut. 28:35; Isa. 1:6\x*the sole of his foot to the crown of his head.
\v 8 And he took \x + \xo 2:8 \xt ch. 41:30 \x*a piece of broken pottery with which to scrape himself while he sat in \x + \xo 2:8 \xt ch. 42:6; Ezek. 27:30; Jonah 3:6; Matt. 11:21\x*the ashes.
\p
\v 9 Then his wife said to him, “Do you still \x + \xo 2:9 \xt ver. 3 \x*hold fast your integrity? \x + \xo 2:9 \xt [See ver. 5 above]\x*Curse God and die.”
\v 10 But he said to her, “You speak as one of the \x + \xo 2:10 \xt [Ps. 74:18, 22] \x*foolish women would speak. \x + \xo 2:10 \xt [James 5:10, 11] \x*Shall we receive good from God, and shall we not receive evil?”\f + \fr 2:10 \ft Or \fq disaster\ft ; also verse 11\f* \x + \xo 2:10 \xt ch. 1:22 \x*In all this Job did not \x + \xo 2:10 \xt [Ps. 39:1]\x*sin with his lips.
\s1 Job’s Three Friends
\p
\v 11 Now when Job’s three \x + \xo 2:11 \xt [Prov. 17:17] \x*friends heard of all this evil that had come upon him, they came each from his own place, Eliphaz \x + \xo 2:11 \xt See 1 Chr. 1:45 \x*the Temanite, Bildad \x + \xo 2:11 \xt Gen. 25:2; 1 Chr. 1:32 \x*the Shuhite, and Zophar the Naamathite. They made an appointment together to come to \x + \xo 2:11 \xt ch. 42:11; [Rom. 12:15]\x*show him sympathy and comfort him.
\v 12 And when they saw him from a distance, they did not recognize him. And they raised their voices and wept, and they \x + \xo 2:12 \xt See Gen. 37:29 \x*tore their robes and sprinkled \x + \xo 2:12 \xt See Josh. 7:6; Neh. 9:1; Lam. 2:10; Ezek. 27:30\x*dust on their heads toward heaven.
\v 13 And they sat with him on the ground \x + \xo 2:13 \xt Ezek. 3:15; [Gen. 50:10]\x*seven days and seven nights, and no one spoke a word to him, for they saw that his suffering was very great.
